I haven't heard anyone talk about busting up an existing camp.<br>
<br>
The problem is.. the list... not who is there now, but why is the person 10 spots down more deserving than someone in SF ready to go after the current camp is over?<br>
<br>
If kildare *is* camping Ragefire anyone trying to jump is an ass.  This is completely irregardless of the list.  It's jumping an existing camp.  <br>
<br>
If Kildare gets Rage and then 2 (or 3 or 4 or 40) clerics are there hoping for the next rage... who decides who is next?  This is what the list is trying to solve but it's turning into bullying  and monopolizing at this point.  You *will* get ppl not willing to go on a 40-long and growing list.  You *will* get ppl that ride other folk's work to coast to their rage on the list, while someone else ready and able and willing to put in the work themselves gets insulted and &quot;blacklisted&quot;.  <br>
<br>
It was brought up to shorten the list to 2 or 3 clerics tops then random to fill the 'next' slot every time rage dies.   This is deemed &quot;unfair&quot; only by folks that get to make the long list.  This is not coincidental.  <br>
<br>
It always sucks when somebody monopolizes something, but it's always great to be a monopoly.  <br>
<br>
Personally, I support whatever my teammate-cleric wants in regards to the list and ffa on Rage.  We have 3 clerics on the list currently.  If a cleric wants to hard-camp the mob outside the list I support that also. I won't condone stealing an existing camp, but a cleric there when/before Rage dies has as much right to the next Rage as anyone.<br>
<br>
The list is an option, it's not an authority.  I like the idea behind it, I think it's an admirable effort, but it's getting topheavy and the bigger the list gets, and the less flexible and more antagonistic the list-users get to new clerics... the closer it gets to failing. <p>Gurunt Bangoo <Wraith>
